SUMMARY:Winter Walk Ward Island to Hanlan's Point
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Bike Meetup\n12.5 km walk from Ward Island to Hanlan's
  Point. Saturday March 28\, 2026\n\n1 PM meet near Roy Woods restaurant in
  the food court at Union Station near the York St. entrance.\n\n1 PM to 2 
 PM: Eat at Union Station food court.\n\n2 PM From Union station\, catch th
 e [509 Harbourfront](https://www.google.com/search?q=509+Harbourfront&rlz=
 1C1RXMK_enCA1182CA1182&ie=UTF-8&ved=2ahUKEwj6yPr6h8uSAxUtwvACHfgaBgIQgK4Qe
 gQIARAC) or [510 Spadina](https://www.google.com/search?q=510+Spadina&rlz=
 1C1RXMK_enCA1182CA1182&ie=UTF-8&ved=2ahUKEwj6yPr6h8uSAxUtwvACHfgaBgIQgK4Qe
 gQIARAD) streetcars to the Jack Layton Ferry terminal.\n\nCatch the ferry 
 to Ward's Island. Proceed to walk to Hanlan's point. Catch the ferry back 
 to the mainland.\n\nRoute Map with GPX Download:\nhttps://www.komoot.com/t
 our/2776019044\n\nWear loose fitting winter clothing: coat\, hat\, gloves\
 , snow pants\, thick socks\, waterproof thermal lined boots with non slip 
 soles. If necessary put warmers in your gloves and boots. Bring water.\n\n
 Chris 647 453 3327
